# NOTE: Keep this list short (~8 entries). Remove old ones as new ones land.
CHANGELOG = [
    "b425: sheet_intake slicer gains --min-variance for flat opaque sheets. The alpha-based blank skip is useless on RGB sheets with a baked background, so background-only cells weren't being dropped. --min-variance also skips cells whose luminance std-dev is below a (sheet-specific) threshold. Validated on the delabeled demon sheet: offset 64,64 + --min-variance 13 sliced 219 clean demon cells and skipped 6 empties, no wall-torch decorations or blue grid frames. (Confirmed via pixel sampling that shipped monster sprites are opaque RGB on warm-grey stone ~52,51,49 -- NOT transparent -- so the demon sheet's ~42,53,54 background is a near-match and needs no keying.)",
    "b424: sheet_intake slicer gains --offset-x / --offset-y so labeled sheets work. A real sprite sheet came in as a 16x16 grid of 64px cells where row 0 holds column-number labels and column 0 holds row-letter labels (sprites fill the 15x15 block from pixel 64,64). The old symmetric --margin couldn't skip a top/left label gutter without also eating the right/bottom edge; the new top-left-only offsets cut a clean 15x15 = 225 sprites with no label bleed. (Note for that particular sheet: it's flat RGB with an opaque textured-stone background baked in, so the cells aren't transparent and can't be chroma-keyed cleanly -- it needs re-exporting with alpha before the sprites are game-ready; the tool itself is correct.)",
    "b423: sprite-sheet intake pipeline (dev tooling). New sprite_package/sheet_intake/ turns a raw sprite sheet into reserve sprites in two steps: slice_and_pick.py carves the sheet into a grid (auto-skips blank/transparent cells, handles --cell-size or --grid ROWSxCOLS plus --margin/--spacing) and builds a mobile multi-select picker (sheet_picker.html, lazy-rendered) where every non-blank cell starts selected and you tap to drop the junk; add_to_reserve.py takes the saved selection, auto-detects the category PID prefix, assigns fresh PIDs above the GLOBAL max (in-game pool + every reserve manifest, so no collisions), copies the kept cells into assets/sprites/reserve/<category>/, and updates that category's manifest.json + libraries/<category>_library.json. From there build_monster_picker.py surfaces them as assignment candidates. Per-run intermediates (staging/, sheet_picker.html, sheet_selection.json) are gitignored; persisting reserve art across fresh checkouts still needs a repack_bundle.sh re-publish. No gameplay/APK behavior change.",
    "b422: applied the user's hand-picked sprites for 5 of the 30 new deep-dungeon monsters (the other 25 auto-picks were kept). Via the b421 monster picker: Hundred-Eyed Watcher -> MN0630 (a proper floating eyeball), Starspawn Aberration -> MN3494 (pale many-armed horror), Cataclysm Fiend -> MN2904 (flaming-sword demon), Soulflayer Wraith -> MN1784 (ghostly spirit), Voidmaw Devourer -> MN1792 (a maw of teeth). apply_picks.py ran the full pipeline (PNG -> sprite_picks overlay + bundle mirror, library reserve->chosen, both _MONSTERS_MAP copies, pool regenerated from scratch). The 5 superseded auto-pick PNGs were pruned from the overlay; pool stays at 1321 in-game entries with no orphans.",
    "b421: deep-monster balance pass (playtest follow-up to b420) + a sprite picker for the new mobs. (1) Tomb-guardian fix: the undead-guardian spawn banded undead by template *level* against the *floor number*, which never matched past floor ~14 and fell through to a uniform-random draw over the ENTIRE undead roster -- so now that the deep tiers added level 12-15 liches/wraiths, a floor-25 tomb could roll a 1430 HP / 413 ATK one-shotter (or a trivial 32 HP Skeleton). Rewrote it to pick undead whose spawn tier actually covers the floor, falling back to the deepest undead at/below the floor. Deep tombs now get floor-appropriate keepers. (2) Tier-15 elite monsters (Elder Starspawn, Infernal Warlord, Nightmare Lich, ...) pushed from floors 38-49 to 43-49 -- at 322 ATK they out-classed the old floor-38 difficulty and 3-shot maxed casters; tier 14 now carries 38-42. (3) Champion spawn caps its source floor at 30 so the flat 2x multiplier never lands on a baked tier-14/15 monster (a CHAMPION CATACLYSM FIEND would have been 3300 HP / 644 ATK). Tooling: new sprite_package/picks_recent/build_monster_picker.py builds a mobile picker (picker_monsters.html) showing each of the 30 new monsters + all 1,428 reserve monster sprites so the auto-assigned art can be confirmed or swapped; apply_picks.py now supports the monsters category end-to-end.",
    "b420: deep-dungeon monster overhaul -- killed the 'Hardened/Savage/Dread/Mythic' evolution-prefix system that re-skinned low-level mobs to fill the bottom half of the dungeon. Replaced it with genuine variety: the monster roster grew from 85 to 115 unique creatures via 30 brand-new tier-11-to-15 horrors (Voidspawn Brute, Cinderborn Efreet, Illithid Overmind, Necrarch Lich, Crimson Wyrmlord, Elder Starspawn, Infernal Warlord, Cataclysm Fiend, ...), each with its own baked-in stats, elements, special attacks, and reserve-promoted sprite. MONSTER_SPAWN_FLOOR_RANGE now defines 16 overlapping tiers across all 50 floors (was 11 crammed by floor 24); every floor draws from 12-50 distinct monsters. Stats are baked into templates -- deep floors are lethal because they spawn real monsters at real stats (HP up to 1650, ATK up to 322), not multiplied weaklings -- so the runtime evolution multiplier + name prefix are gone entirely. The endgame difficulty ceiling is preserved (anchored to the old curve); the mid-game is honest base stats rather than inflated reskins. Champion spawns now pull from the floor's own tier pool so deep champions stay threatening. 30 reserve monster sprites promoted from the sprite-assets-v1 bundle into the committed assets/sprite_picks/monsters/ overlay; pool 1291 -> 1321. Several deep monsters carry undead-keyword names (Hollow/Necrarch/Sepulchral/Nightmare Lich, Cryptborn/Soulflayer Wraith) so tomb guardians scale into the deep floors too.",
    "b419: three cleanups. (1) Fey-garden bug: room_actions.py harvested an inline 6-item loot table (Moonbell Flower, Starshade Root, ...) that was never registered in INGREDIENT_TEMPLATES and had no sprites, so fey gardens dropped unsprited pool-fallback ingredients while the 8 sprited canonical FEY_GARDEN_INGREDIENTS (Fey Blossom, Phoenix Feather, Unicorn Tear, ...) could never be obtained. Switched the harvest to the canonical list (already imported) and deleted the dead duplicate copy in game_state.py. Fey gardens now drop the higher-value sprited ingredients. (2) SPELL_TEMPLATES dedup: items.py carried a stale 55-spell copy that had diverged in balance from item_templates.py's 53-spell list (8 spells had different mana costs / Time Stop reworked / Acid Splash element). Per user direction, made Mage Armor + Spectral Hand real player spells by adding them to the canonical item_templates.py list (now 55), deleted items.py's copy, and redirected all imports (playtest_harness + items.py internal scroll-gen / id-system) to the single source. The two caster buffs are now purchasable from spell vendors. (3) Dead sprite-slot removal: audited the 17 suspected-dead sprite-map entries and found 12 were FALSE POSITIVES -- DEATH KNIGHT/DIVINE AVATAR/TREASURE GOLEM are legendary shard bosses (decorated names like ' DEATH KNIGHT' resolve via the prefix-stripping resolver), and LOST SOUL/WANDERING GHOST/POLTERGEIST/RESTLESS SPIRIT/MUMMIFIED KING/TOMB WRAITH/SKELETAL CHAMPION/SPECTRAL KNIGHT/Mimic are live spirit-ambush + tomb-guardian spawns. Only 5 were genuinely dead (Chimera, Hook Horror, Hydra, Lizardman -- legacy D&D monsters never spawned; Bow -- an ORGANIC_WEAPONS keyword with no item). Removed those 5 from BOTH the runtime maps (wizardscavern/sprites/) and the promotion snippets (sprite_package/code/), keeping the two in sync, and regenerated the pool (1304 -> 1291, dropping 13 unreferenced sprites).",
    "b418: kill the 109 MB bundle re-publish chore by introducing a per-pick PNG overlay committed to the repo. Picker rounds no longer need a fresh sprite-assets-v1 zip upload to make picks survive fresh checkouts. New dir assets/sprite_picks/<cat>/PID_Name_v0.png holds every PNG picked since the last base-bundle re-publish (currently 21 PNGs, ~412 KB total). sprite_package/code/promote_all_sprites.py:index_in_game_pngs() now scans both the bundle's in_game/by_category/ and this overlay dir, with overlay entries winning over the base for the same PID, so canonical_pool_full.pkl rebuilds correctly even when the bundle on the GitHub Release is months stale. Verified by simulating a fresh checkout: deleted the picked PIDs from the bundle, regenerated the pool, and confirmed all 1304 in-game entries (matching the live tree) still resolve. sprite_package/picks_recent/apply_picks.py writes picked PNGs to assets/sprite_picks/ as the canonical destination and mirrors into the bundle's in_game/by_category/ + by_item/ views so repack_bundle.sh still produces a consistent zip when you DO want to compact picks into a new base. Going forward: pick -> git push, no bundle upload. Re-publish only when you want to compact the overlay -- maybe quarterly. .gitignore whitelisted assets/sprite_picks/ (the parent assets/sprites/ stays gitignored).",
]
